title: The Nose [Нос] Metropolitan Opera 2013 Dmitri Shostakovich 1928
description: The Nose, Op. 15, (Russian: Нос, translit. Nos[a 1]), is Dmitri Shostakovich's first opera, a satirical work completed in 1928 based on Nikolai Gogol's story of the same name (1836). Acclaimed artist William Kentridge directed and designed this visually dazzling Met premiere production of Shostakovich’s satirical opera, adapted from the classic short story by Nikolai Gogol. Baritone Paulo Szot leads the cast as Kovalyov, the hapless bureaucrat whose nose has mysteriously gone missing. Alexander Lewis and Andrey Popov co-star, and Pavel Smelkov conducts. https://metopera.org/season/on-demand/opera/?upc=811357016824
